Package jetbrains.exodus.env

Interface ContextualStore

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Store
    public interface ContextualStore
extends Store
    ContextualStore is a Store created by ContextualEnvironment. Just like ContextualEnvironment, it is aware of transaction started in current thread. ContextualStore overloads all Store's methods with the ones that don't accept transaction instance.
    See Also:
    ContextualEnvironment, Transaction, Store

      • put

        boolean put​(@NotNull
            @NotNull ByteIterable key,
            @NotNull
            @NotNull ByteIterable value)
        Puts specified key/value pair into the ContextualStore and returns the result. For stores with key duplicates, it returns true if the pair didn't exist in the ContextualStore. For stores without key duplicates, it returns true if the key didn't exist or the new value differs from the existing one.
        With duplicatesWithout duplicates
        The key existsAdds pair, if the value didn't existOverwrites value
        The key doesn't existAdds pairAdds pair
        Parameters:
        key - not null key
        value - not null value
        Returns:
        true if specified pair was added or value by the key was overwritten.

      • putRight

        void putRight​(@NotNull
              @NotNull ByteIterable key,
              @NotNull
              @NotNull ByteIterable value)
        Can be used if it is a priori known that the key is definitely greater than any other key in the ContextualStore. In that case, no search is been done before insertion, so putRight() can perform several times faster than put(ByteIterable, ByteIterable). It can be useful for auto-generated keys.
        Parameters:
        key - key
        value - value

      • add

        boolean add​(@NotNull
            @NotNull ByteIterable key,
            @NotNull
            @NotNull ByteIterable value)
        Adds key/value pair to the ContextualStore if the key doesn't exist. For stores with and without key duplicates, it returns true if and only if the key doesn't exists. So it never overwrites value of existing key.

      • delete

        boolean delete​(@NotNull
               @NotNull ByteIterable key)
        For stores without key duplicates, deletes single key/value pair and returns true if a pair was deleted. For stores with key duplicates, it deletes all pairs with the given key and returns true if any was deleted. To delete particular key/value pair, use cursors.
        Parameters:
        key - key
        Returns:
        true if a key/value pair was deleted.
